.TH "WebGLRenderingContext.lineWidth" "JS" "April 8, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.lineWidth \- WebGLRenderingContext: lineWidth()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLRenderingContext.lineWidth()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
WebGL API sets the line width of rasterized lines.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Warning:\f[R] The webgl spec, based on the OpenGL ES 2.0/3.0 specs
points out that the minimum and maximum width for a line is
implementation defined.
The maximum minimum width is allowed to be 1.0.
The minimum maximum width is also allowed to be 1.0.
Because of these implementation defined limits it is not recommended to
use line widths other than 1.0 since there is no guarantee any
user\[cq]s browser will display any other width.
.PP
As of January 2017 most implementations of WebGL only support a minimum
of 1 and a maximum of 1 as the technology they are based on has these
same limits.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
lineWidth(width)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]width\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLfloat\f[R] specifying the width of rasterized lines.
Default value: 1.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
Setting the line width:
.IP
.EX
gl.lineWidth(5);
.EE
.PP
Getting the line width:
.IP
.EX
gl.getParameter(gl.LINE_WIDTH);
.EE
.PP
Getting the range of available widths.
Returns a \f[CR]Float32Array\f[R].
.IP
.EX
gl.getParameter(gl.ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE);
.EE
